OL,3,CSummer Solstice 2026: Why June 21st is
OL,4,Cthe longest day of the year?
OL,6,FTomorrow marks the arrival of the
OL,7,Fsummer solstice - the longest day of
OL,8,Fthe year.
OL,10,FIt marks the onset of summer, and it's
OL,11,Fa cause for celebration. Each solstice
OL,12,Fthousands of people head to
OL,13,FStonehenge, which is famous for its
OL,14,Falignment on sunrise on the special
OL,15,Fday.
OL,17,FTomorrow's solstice will be taking
OL,18,Fplace at 4:52am.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G1/6
