OL,3,CSummer Solstice 2026: Why June 21st is
OL,4,Cthe longest day of the year?
OL,6,FAccording to Heritage England, the
OL,7,Fstones near Amesbury in Wiltshire were
OL,8,Fset up in about 2500 BC and designed
OL,9,Fto align with the movements of the sun.
OL,11,FStanding in the centre of the monument
OL,12,Fat summer solstice, the sun rises just
OL,13,Fto the left of a large standing stone
OL,14,Foutside the stone circle, known as the
OL,15,FHeel Stone, seen through a gap in the
OL,16,Fouter sarsen circle.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/6
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
