OL,3,CSummer Solstice 2026: Why June 21st is
OL,4,Cthe longest day of the year?
OL,6,FIt is likely that people gathered at
OL,7,FStonehenge at both midsummer and
OL,8,Fmidwinter solstices to conduct rituals
OL,9,Fand ceremonies relating to the
OL,10,Fchanging seasons, the sun and the sky.
OL,12,FThe longest day of the year was likely
OL,13,Fa time of celebration, with warm
OL,14,Fnights and long daylight making it the
OL,15,Fperfect time to gather together.
OL,17,FWhat's the history of Stonehenge?
OL,19,FThe purpose of Stonehenge is unknown
OL,20,Fto us. It has no obvious practical
OL,21,Fpurpose.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/6
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
